1
00:00:00,501 --> 00:00:02,586
Eli rarely talks to others.

2
00:00:02,670 --> 00:00:03,796
But he's comfortable with you.

3
00:00:03,879 --> 00:00:06,549
Maybe we have the same vibe.

4
00:00:06,632 --> 00:00:08,718
-We both lost a loved one.
-Who's your father?

5
00:00:08,801 --> 00:00:11,345
He's Manu Cortez. The new chief of police.

6
00:00:26,527 --> 00:00:28,446
-I didn't want to lose you!
-He confessed.

7
00:00:28,529 --> 00:00:30,781
-Why don't you believe him?
-Not all confessions are true.

8
00:00:30,865 --> 00:00:32,074
Let's put Sam to rest.

9
00:00:32,158 --> 00:00:34,201
If it was that easy,
I would've done it a long time ago.

10
00:00:34,285 --> 00:00:35,786
I've said everything I needed to say.

11
00:00:35,870 --> 00:00:36,954
Who are you taking the fall for?

12
00:00:38,205 --> 00:00:40,291
I'm sure this case has kept you up
for nights on end.

13
00:00:40,374 --> 00:00:44,128
Some things are better left closed.

14
00:00:44,211 --> 00:00:46,505
Sam Ignacio's case isn't closed yet.

15
00:00:46,589 --> 00:00:47,423
You said it yourself.

16
00:00:47,506 --> 00:00:49,341
We don't have enough evidence.

17
00:00:49,425 --> 00:00:51,886
I just said that to keep you
away from the case.

18
00:00:51,969 --> 00:00:52,803
It's too dangerous.

19
00:00:52,887 --> 00:00:54,221
I want to find evidence,

20
00:00:54,305 --> 00:00:55,806
so I'm just playing along for now.

21
00:00:56,682 --> 00:00:58,267
Damn it!

22
00:01:04,774 --> 00:01:06,150
Kyle.

23
00:01:06,233 --> 00:01:07,860
Man, what took you so long?

24
00:01:07,943 --> 00:01:09,445
I thought you weren't coming.

25
00:01:09,528 --> 00:01:11,155
-Jeez.
-You're too impatient!

26
00:01:11,238 --> 00:01:12,573
I have it.

27
00:01:12,656 --> 00:01:14,158
Here, look.

28
00:01:16,577 --> 00:01:18,204
Is that it?

29
00:01:18,287 --> 00:01:19,663
This is top quality.

30
00:01:19,747 --> 00:01:22,041
Hey, that's good stuff.

31
00:01:22,792 --> 00:01:24,126
Mind if I have some?

32
00:01:24,752 --> 00:01:25,753
Don't.

33
00:01:25,836 --> 00:01:27,671
It's my dad's. I just borrowed it.

34
00:01:27,755 --> 00:01:29,548
So stingy!

35
00:01:29,632 --> 00:01:31,091
Aren't we friends now?

36
00:01:34,887 --> 00:01:37,473
Hey, you're short.

37
00:01:37,556 --> 00:01:40,392
Can you add more? I came all this way.

38
00:01:40,476 --> 00:01:42,269
Bro, I'm your regular.

39
00:01:42,353 --> 00:01:43,938
Come on.

40
00:01:44,021 --> 00:01:45,523
Don't try scamming me.

41
00:01:45,606 --> 00:01:48,150
What did you say? I'm scamming you?

42
00:01:48,234 --> 00:01:49,401
Hey.

43
00:01:49,485 --> 00:01:52,571
Kid, you should watch your mouth.

44
00:01:55,699 --> 00:01:56,742
Hey!

45
00:02:08,963 --> 00:02:10,798
Damn, this really is good.

46
00:02:11,632 --> 00:02:14,510
Hey, don't act tough with me.

47
00:02:15,261 --> 00:02:18,347
This might reach your dad, you know?

48
00:02:18,430 --> 00:02:19,557
Here.

49
00:06:14,416 --> 00:06:15,959
Good evening, Detective.

50
00:06:16,043 --> 00:06:18,629
Good evening, Mr. Carpio.

51
00:06:19,588 --> 00:06:21,048
What brings you to my home?

52
00:06:21,840 --> 00:06:25,010
I'm sorry, but I'm here for Kyle.

53
00:06:34,978 --> 00:06:36,647
You know my son?

54
00:06:38,649 --> 00:06:39,650
Yes.

55
00:06:41,193 --> 00:06:42,236
From Pia.

56
00:06:42,319 --> 00:06:45,072
My daughter.

57
00:06:46,740 --> 00:06:49,368
I was going to pick her up.
I thought she was here.

58
00:06:50,160 --> 00:06:51,286
Kyle!

59
00:06:52,746 --> 00:06:54,456
Uh, Pia's my classmate,

60
00:06:54,540 --> 00:06:58,252
and we're also partners on a project.

61
00:06:58,335 --> 00:07:02,673
But I left her at school earlier, sir.

62
00:07:03,382 --> 00:07:04,716
Ah, is that so?

63
00:07:05,551 --> 00:07:08,011
Her phone is off, I can't reach her.

64
00:07:12,766 --> 00:07:14,977
I'm sorry to disturb you.

65
00:07:15,853 --> 00:07:17,020
It's all right, Mr. Carpio.

66
00:07:17,104 --> 00:07:20,065
If you need help finding your daughter,
just let me know.

67
00:07:20,149 --> 00:07:21,859
All right, thank you.

68
00:07:21,942 --> 00:07:23,485
Maybe she's home already.

69
00:09:25,357 --> 00:09:27,109
You damn bastard!

70
00:09:27,192 --> 00:09:28,485
How dare you!

71
00:09:29,695 --> 00:09:31,530
You're lucky your father was there.

72
00:09:35,117 --> 00:09:36,743
You should consider yourself lucky

73
00:09:37,828 --> 00:09:40,205
my father hasn't gotten hold
of Ms. Ignacio's phone.

74
00:09:41,623 --> 00:09:44,084
A tracker? Really, Mr. Carpio?

75
00:09:45,294 --> 00:09:48,964
The next time you try to outsmart me,
I'm going to choose.

76
00:09:49,506 --> 00:09:53,885
I'm giving this phone
to either my father or Pia.

77
00:10:22,789 --> 00:10:23,957
Uh, Jackie…

78
00:10:25,167 --> 00:10:27,544
-Can this still fit?
-Give it to me.

79
00:10:29,087 --> 00:10:31,673
Anton, please check
if the food I asked to put

80
00:10:31,757 --> 00:10:33,592
in the cooler is complete.

81
00:10:36,845 --> 00:10:37,929
It's complete.

82
00:10:38,555 --> 00:10:41,641
Let's pass by the market because
I still need to buy some vegetables.

83
00:10:41,725 --> 00:10:43,810
Luckily, there is no rain forecast.

84
00:10:43,894 --> 00:10:46,521
But, in case it rains,
I brought board games

85
00:10:46,605 --> 00:10:50,150
so we can do something with the kids
if we get stuck in the tent.

86
00:10:50,233 --> 00:10:52,819
-I'll take this downstairs.
-Oh, wait.

87
00:10:52,903 --> 00:10:55,072
I almost forgot the salad.

88
00:10:58,700 --> 00:11:00,202
By the way, Anton.

89
00:11:00,285 --> 00:11:03,330
Anton, don't forget the kite.
We have to bring that.

90
00:11:03,413 --> 00:11:05,290
Okay, uh…

91
00:11:05,374 --> 00:11:08,960
I'll just take this downstairs.
Then I'll get the kite and the kids.

92
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:15,634
Pia, if we catch it later,
you'll see the beautiful sunrise there.

93
00:11:15,717 --> 00:11:17,552
Here, Pa.

94
00:11:17,636 --> 00:11:18,512
-Pia.
-Ma?

95
00:11:18,595 --> 00:11:19,888
Are you sure we brought everything?

96
00:11:21,223 --> 00:11:22,307
I checked everything.

97
00:11:23,225 --> 00:11:25,435
Anton, the food in the fridge
that I mentioned,

98
00:11:25,519 --> 00:11:27,270
did you put them all in the cooler?

99
00:11:28,063 --> 00:11:29,106
I checked everything.

100
00:11:38,865 --> 00:11:42,327
No fighting, no drama…

101
00:11:43,286 --> 00:11:45,914
We'll forget about our problems.

102
00:11:50,502 --> 00:11:51,336
Matt.

103
00:11:54,131 --> 00:11:55,173
Matt…

104
00:11:56,591 --> 00:11:58,468
Did you hear what I said?

105
00:11:59,928 --> 00:12:01,054
Yes.

106
00:12:07,394 --> 00:12:08,437
Eli.

107
00:12:11,898 --> 00:12:14,860
In case of an emergency,
you know what to do.

108
00:12:15,902 --> 00:12:16,945
Okay?

109
00:12:18,447 --> 00:12:19,322
Son.

110
00:12:19,906 --> 00:12:20,782
Let's go.

111
00:12:21,825 --> 00:12:23,034
Come on.

112
00:12:56,943 --> 00:12:58,570
Pa, it's beautiful!

113
00:13:09,206 --> 00:13:11,666
Thank you for this trip.

114
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:13,460
You're welcome.

115
00:13:31,728 --> 00:13:33,855
Mama has a small request.

116
00:13:33,939 --> 00:13:35,941
While we're here,

117
00:13:36,441 --> 00:13:37,692
I think…

118
00:13:38,777 --> 00:13:40,862
no one uses their cell phones.

119
00:13:42,447 --> 00:13:43,532
Ma…

120
00:13:49,162 --> 00:13:53,041
And also, we shouldn't do work for now.

121
00:13:57,170 --> 00:13:58,004
That's right.

122
00:13:59,130 --> 00:14:01,925
Let's focus on family first, okay?

123
00:14:02,968 --> 00:14:04,469
Give me your phones.

124
00:14:04,553 --> 00:14:06,846
Wait, Pa. I'll just send a reply to Kyle.

125
00:14:13,061 --> 00:14:16,606
For the school project, Pa. Wait a minute.

126
00:14:25,991 --> 00:14:26,825
Matt.

127
00:14:36,459 --> 00:14:41,381
Do all the activities
you want to do, okay?

128
00:14:41,464 --> 00:14:43,008
However, come evening…

129
00:14:44,426 --> 00:14:47,470
We'll make a bonfire and s'mores.

130
00:14:49,014 --> 00:14:51,683
I want s'mores.

131
00:15:06,740 --> 00:15:09,618
It's flying. Matt, lock it already.

132
00:15:09,701 --> 00:15:11,036
Okay.

133
00:15:11,119 --> 00:15:13,830
Wait, before you lock it,
is the weight equal?

134
00:15:14,539 --> 00:15:16,041
There, lock it now. Bury the tent peg.

135
00:15:18,376 --> 00:15:19,544
Thank you.

136
00:15:21,171 --> 00:15:23,214
Make sure it's locked tightly.

137
00:15:25,508 --> 00:15:28,345
Here feels happier.

138
00:15:31,097 --> 00:15:32,641
Bury the peg properly.

139
00:15:36,186 --> 00:15:41,024
Can I ask you something
about your butterfly drawings?

140
00:15:48,698 --> 00:15:49,699
Answer that next time.

141
00:16:03,338 --> 00:16:04,673
Here's the ice.

142
00:16:11,680 --> 00:16:17,936
I'm scared it might fall.

143
00:16:24,484 --> 00:16:25,568
Eli.

144
00:16:26,444 --> 00:16:27,987
Your sister is right.

145
00:16:35,787 --> 00:16:42,544
If you're calm, you can think better.

146
00:16:50,135 --> 00:16:51,177
Matteo!

147
00:16:52,053 --> 00:16:54,639
-Why don't you help?
-You can manage.

148
00:16:59,352 --> 00:17:01,354
Come on, I need your help.

149
00:17:03,231 --> 00:17:05,525
What help?

150
00:17:05,608 --> 00:17:08,528
I need more flat stones. And smooth.

151
00:17:08,611 --> 00:17:11,239
Help me find more.

152
00:17:12,031 --> 00:17:14,200
It's hard to do what you want.

153
00:17:14,284 --> 00:17:15,618
Let's not bother.

154
00:17:16,119 --> 00:17:17,495
Please.

155
00:17:18,413 --> 00:17:19,956
Matteo.

156
00:17:20,039 --> 00:17:21,875
Come on, don't be a killjoy.

157
00:17:25,587 --> 00:17:27,213
-All right, all right, fine.
-See?

158
00:17:30,467 --> 00:17:32,302
What do we need to do?

159
00:17:32,385 --> 00:17:35,555
Here. Match our stones.

160
00:17:38,016 --> 00:17:39,601
Ouch.

161
00:18:11,841 --> 00:18:13,593
You're quiet.

162
00:18:17,263 --> 00:18:18,556
Ma.

163
00:18:20,517 --> 00:18:21,851
Is there still a chance?

164
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:26,815
Is there still a chance
I could redeem myself?

165
00:18:29,859 --> 00:18:33,446
What do you think I should do
to erase my bad image?

166
00:18:35,698 --> 00:18:36,825
Matt.

167
00:18:43,456 --> 00:18:44,707
Because, Ma…

168
00:18:46,626 --> 00:18:48,753
Every time people look at me,

169
00:18:49,254 --> 00:18:50,630
you and Papa, for example…

170
00:18:51,673 --> 00:18:53,007
I can clearly see…

171
00:18:54,509 --> 00:18:55,718
the judgment…

172
00:18:58,137 --> 00:18:59,681
the disappointment…

173
00:19:06,563 --> 00:19:09,190
Maybe that's why it's so hard
for me to move on.

174
00:19:13,319 --> 00:19:14,529
First…

175
00:19:17,156 --> 00:19:20,201
mistakes are not erased overnight.

176
00:19:24,372 --> 00:19:27,250
Second, we're very disappointed.

177
00:19:30,628 --> 00:19:34,257
But it's wrong of you
to think we're judging you.

178
00:19:40,013 --> 00:19:41,973
That does not happen overnight.

179
00:19:50,315 --> 00:19:53,109
But what if I don't get better?

180
00:19:54,736 --> 00:19:57,322
Then we failed as your parents.

181
00:19:58,615 --> 00:20:01,492
Because it means
that we didn't raise you properly.

182
00:20:03,202 --> 00:20:05,622
Do you think we'll let that happen?

183
00:20:12,086 --> 00:20:13,922
You'll get through this, son.

184
00:20:17,050 --> 00:20:18,509
You got this.

185
00:20:28,728 --> 00:20:30,563
Thank you so much, Ma.

186
00:20:32,857 --> 00:20:35,234
Thank you for not abandoning me

187
00:20:36,027 --> 00:20:38,696
even though I've broken your trust.

188
00:20:41,824 --> 00:20:45,036
Thank you for not letting go of my hands.

189
00:20:46,955 --> 00:20:49,374
I always tell Eli, don't I?

190
00:20:49,457 --> 00:20:51,042
That I'm here.

191
00:20:52,752 --> 00:20:55,254
We're here for him.

192
00:20:56,047 --> 00:20:58,174
But I hope you and Pia know

193
00:20:59,384 --> 00:21:01,594
that the same goes for you both.

194
00:21:30,289 --> 00:21:31,290
What's that?

195
00:21:34,377 --> 00:21:37,380
I'm just taking a break
from all the academic books.

196
00:21:38,256 --> 00:21:40,425
I'm glad you're having fun.

197
00:21:43,261 --> 00:21:44,721
But don't overdo it, all right?

198
00:21:51,185 --> 00:21:54,022
Pa, if you're worried about Kyle…

199
00:21:55,898 --> 00:21:58,609
He's not courting me. Relax.

200
00:22:00,903 --> 00:22:03,156
Pia, I've noticed that…

201
00:22:03,239 --> 00:22:05,491
you seem to be getting close to him.

202
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:07,285
I hope that…

203
00:22:08,202 --> 00:22:10,163
I hope he's not a bad influence on you.

204
00:22:25,178 --> 00:22:26,262
That's all I wanted to say--

205
00:22:27,555 --> 00:22:30,683
You know, Pa, acting like a cool dad
doesn't suit you.

206
00:22:31,934 --> 00:22:34,645
All right, fine. I'm not a cool dad.

207
00:22:35,521 --> 00:22:37,565
But whether you like it or not, Pia,

208
00:22:38,691 --> 00:22:41,277
our family will have
to get to know Kyle first.

209
00:22:44,739 --> 00:22:46,574
And don't be mad at your brother anymore.

210
00:22:47,116 --> 00:22:48,576
He's just trying to protect you.

211
00:22:53,206 --> 00:22:54,540
Okay, Pa.

212
00:22:59,045 --> 00:23:00,379
Come here, you.

213
00:23:01,547 --> 00:23:03,633
What's that about anyway?
You keep reading it.

214
00:23:25,655 --> 00:23:26,739
We have a surprise for you.

215
00:23:27,281 --> 00:23:28,533
What is it?

216
00:23:38,709 --> 00:23:42,171
-I caught it myself.
-Showoff!

217
00:23:43,381 --> 00:23:45,967
Thank you, Matteo! Thank you, Pia!

218
00:23:56,352 --> 00:23:58,604
Come on, Pia. Let's go cook outside.

219
00:24:09,198 --> 00:24:10,575
I'll leave you to it, okay?

220
00:24:10,658 --> 00:24:12,201
I'll just get more sticks.

221
00:24:25,464 --> 00:24:27,008
What're you looking for? Let me help.

222
00:24:27,091 --> 00:24:29,260
I was looking for the kite.
Where did you put it?

223
00:24:31,095 --> 00:24:33,264
Shoot, I think I left it at home.

224
00:24:34,473 --> 00:24:35,600
Come on, Anton.

225
00:24:36,434 --> 00:24:38,603
Eli was looking forward to it the most.

226
00:24:38,686 --> 00:24:41,564
It's the reason why
he wanted to come here.

227
00:24:42,064 --> 00:24:43,733
I told you, I forgot.

228
00:24:45,234 --> 00:24:46,527
Let's just make something else.

229
00:24:46,611 --> 00:24:49,030
Maybe a paper plane or some board games.

230
00:24:49,113 --> 00:24:50,573
He'll have fun with those too.

231
00:24:51,908 --> 00:24:53,492
Explain yourself to him.

232
00:24:54,368 --> 00:24:56,913
Sure. I'll go talk to Eli.

233
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:21,437
I should've just taken it myself.

234
00:25:24,482 --> 00:25:27,735
I said I'll talk to Eli.
It's probably no big deal to him.

235
00:25:27,818 --> 00:25:29,320
You don't get it.

236
00:25:29,403 --> 00:25:32,073
You have no idea
how important it is to him.

237
00:25:32,156 --> 00:25:34,075
It can't be replaced by paper planes,

238
00:25:34,158 --> 00:25:35,660
by board games,

239
00:25:35,743 --> 00:25:37,995
no matter how many s'mores
you make for him.

240
00:25:38,079 --> 00:25:41,165
Jackie, let's not fight over a mere kite.

241
00:25:43,209 --> 00:25:45,378
There you go again,
blowing things out of proportion.

242
00:25:47,296 --> 00:25:48,631
So I'm in the wrong?

243
00:25:49,840 --> 00:25:50,675
I am.

244
00:25:51,884 --> 00:25:54,136
I'm wrong. You're not.

245
00:25:54,220 --> 00:25:55,763
You are never wrong.

246
00:25:56,514 --> 00:25:59,558
You're always looking for a fault in me
and every chance you find something,

247
00:25:59,642 --> 00:26:01,060
you make a big deal out of it.

248
00:26:02,895 --> 00:26:04,981
You're the one
making a big deal out of it.

249
00:26:06,857 --> 00:26:09,360
Maybe. Maybe I really am, Jackie.

250
00:26:11,946 --> 00:26:14,991
Because I know that kite
means something else to you.

251
00:26:15,074 --> 00:26:16,617
You're just using Eli.

252
00:26:19,912 --> 00:26:22,123
And I know that
you won't run out of reasons

253
00:26:22,206 --> 00:26:24,875
to get mad at me so you could
finally leave me, right?

254
00:26:31,340 --> 00:26:33,467
Watch what you're doing.

255
00:26:33,551 --> 00:26:35,303
It hurts.

256
00:26:35,386 --> 00:26:37,305
Next time, be careful.

257
00:26:37,930 --> 00:26:40,308
Especially when it comes
to getting close to others.

258
00:26:43,602 --> 00:26:45,896
Weird. Did Papa talk to you?

259
00:26:46,814 --> 00:26:49,108
Why are we talking about Kyle
all of a sudden?

260
00:26:49,191 --> 00:26:50,151
See?

261
00:26:50,776 --> 00:26:54,613
I didn't even mention any names,
yet you already know who I'm referring to.

262
00:26:54,697 --> 00:26:57,700
Duh, Kyle's the only person
I've been close to lately.

263
00:26:57,783 --> 00:26:59,410
Don't you feel bad for the kids?

264
00:26:59,493 --> 00:27:00,995
Don't be selfish.

265
00:27:09,795 --> 00:27:13,007
I've endured for so many years
just for you to call me selfish?

266
00:27:13,090 --> 00:27:15,176
You're not the only one suffering.

267
00:27:16,135 --> 00:27:19,472
With every decision I make,
I always consider the kids.

268
00:27:20,222 --> 00:27:22,975
But isn't it wrong that,
every time we face them,

269
00:27:23,059 --> 00:27:26,228
we pretend we're happy,
that we still love each other?

270
00:27:26,312 --> 00:27:29,732
What? You're saying it's better
to ruin this family instead?

271
00:27:29,815 --> 00:27:31,442
Why? Was I the…

272
00:27:31,525 --> 00:27:32,777
The what?

273
00:27:32,860 --> 00:27:34,236
You're the what?

274
00:27:36,364 --> 00:27:38,074
So you admit it.

275
00:27:41,077 --> 00:27:44,955
See? You're not even that close,
but you act like you know him already.

276
00:27:48,042 --> 00:27:50,461
And you're judging someone
you don't even know.

277
00:27:51,462 --> 00:27:53,255
What about it?

278
00:27:53,339 --> 00:27:55,091
Can I not be worried about my sister?

279
00:27:55,674 --> 00:27:56,842
Oh, please.

280
00:27:57,510 --> 00:27:59,178
Not everyone is out to hurt people.

281
00:28:00,763 --> 00:28:04,100
And not everyone reveals
their true selves right away.

282
00:28:05,101 --> 00:28:08,229
Matteo, you're just paranoid.
You're just overreacting.

283
00:28:08,312 --> 00:28:09,855
It's better than being stupid.

284
00:28:10,564 --> 00:28:12,608
Stupid, huh? Well, which one of us
acted stupid over Jem?

285
00:28:19,657 --> 00:28:21,033
Matteo, I'm sorry.

286
00:28:26,080 --> 00:28:27,581
Matteo, I'm sorry.

287
00:28:44,849 --> 00:28:46,142
Look at me.

288
00:28:47,476 --> 00:28:48,978
Look at me, Jackie.

289
00:28:54,900 --> 00:28:57,695
I know you're still blaming me
for my past mistakes.

290
00:28:58,988 --> 00:29:00,322
What about you?

291
00:29:01,782 --> 00:29:03,242
Don't you have anything to hide?

292
00:29:05,661 --> 00:29:07,413
Do you really have a clear conscience?

293
00:29:12,293 --> 00:29:15,421
That's my role in this family, isn't it?

294
00:29:15,504 --> 00:29:18,716
When I make a mistake, it's a big deal.

295
00:29:18,799 --> 00:29:20,259
But when it's you or Eli,

296
00:29:20,342 --> 00:29:22,303
you're given the benefit of the doubt.

297
00:29:24,763 --> 00:29:25,806
Matteo.

298
00:29:26,557 --> 00:29:28,350
I said I'm sorry.

299
00:29:29,101 --> 00:29:30,603
I'll get to know Kyle first.

300
00:29:31,770 --> 00:29:33,647
Let's stop fighting. I'm sorry.

301
00:29:33,731 --> 00:29:34,815
Come on, Matteo.

302
00:29:35,608 --> 00:29:36,692
Matteo.

303
00:29:37,526 --> 00:29:39,069
Wait, hold on.

304
00:29:42,740 --> 00:29:43,908
What do you know?

305
00:29:47,578 --> 00:29:48,996
What I know is that…

306
00:29:52,583 --> 00:29:55,586
you have not forgiven me
for what I did in the past.

307
00:29:56,295 --> 00:29:58,130
I did everything I could
to make it up to you.

308
00:29:58,214 --> 00:30:01,967
I do everything I can
to keep this family together, but you…

309
00:30:04,720 --> 00:30:05,846
you gave up long ago.

310
00:30:10,059 --> 00:30:14,271
How dare you forget
all of the sacrifices I've made.

311
00:30:17,149 --> 00:30:21,862
You know I tried to forget
what you did to me, but it's so hard.

312
00:30:24,073 --> 00:30:26,200
Every time I look at Eli,

313
00:30:27,618 --> 00:30:31,247
all I think is how he's the one
who paid for your sins.

314
00:30:32,957 --> 00:30:35,376
Didn't I still choose to be your wife

315
00:30:35,459 --> 00:30:38,128
even when I stopped loving you
a long time ago?

316
00:30:40,256 --> 00:30:42,716
Even though I've been
putting up with everything

317
00:30:42,800 --> 00:30:44,969
just to keep this family together.

318
00:31:21,171 --> 00:31:23,257
Where did that damn stick go?

319
00:31:34,727 --> 00:31:36,478
Can I have the first aid kit?

320
00:31:37,229 --> 00:31:40,232
Yeah, sure. Pia, the first aid kit.

321
00:31:42,109 --> 00:31:43,235
Come here.

322
00:31:47,406 --> 00:31:48,657
Get the chairs.

323
00:31:56,790 --> 00:31:58,083
I'll do it.

324
00:32:13,223 --> 00:32:14,892
Here, stay still.

325
00:32:15,684 --> 00:32:16,518
That hurts!

326
00:32:56,392 --> 00:32:57,810
Where's Eli? There you are!

327
00:33:03,816 --> 00:33:05,526
-Fa.
-Fa.

328
00:33:05,609 --> 00:33:07,111
-Mi.
-Mi.

329
00:33:07,194 --> 00:33:08,529
-Ly.
-Ly.

330
00:33:08,612 --> 00:33:10,406
Family.

331
00:33:10,489 --> 00:33:11,573
-Family?
-Yes!

332
00:33:42,521 --> 00:33:43,981
Ma, Pa.

333
00:33:45,315 --> 00:33:47,776
What were you talking about?

334
00:33:51,947 --> 00:33:53,073
It's nothing.

335
00:33:53,949 --> 00:33:55,492
Pa, come on.

336
00:33:55,576 --> 00:33:56,994
Does it look like it's nothing?

337
00:33:58,203 --> 00:34:01,331
It's something between your mom and me.
We'll deal with it ourselves.

338
00:34:01,957 --> 00:34:04,710
I thought we wouldn't keep secrets
from each other anymore.

339
00:34:09,423 --> 00:34:12,092
Matt, it's better for you
if you don't know anything.

340
00:34:14,845 --> 00:34:17,431
Matteo, Pia,

341
00:34:17,514 --> 00:34:21,477
children shouldn't always know
about the fights of their parents.

342
00:34:22,436 --> 00:34:24,438
We're just trying to protect you.

343
00:34:26,523 --> 00:34:30,068
Well, how can you protect us
if you're going to split up?

344
00:34:32,696 --> 00:34:34,698
-Pia--
-Ma, Matteo and I heard

345
00:34:34,782 --> 00:34:35,991
what you were talking about.

346
00:34:38,786 --> 00:34:41,038
You said you don't love him anymore.

347
00:34:42,456 --> 00:34:45,709
You said you were just enduring everything
to keep the family together.

348
00:34:52,800 --> 00:34:53,967
Pia…

349
00:35:26,542 --> 00:35:27,751
Eli?

350
00:35:34,716 --> 00:35:37,678
Matteo, Ma, Eli is missing!

351
00:35:37,761 --> 00:35:38,804
What do you mean, gone?

352
00:35:38,887 --> 00:35:40,722
-What do you mean?
-Hurry, let's find him!

353
00:35:48,522 --> 00:35:50,107
-Pia. The jar.
-Ouch.

354
00:35:51,108 --> 00:35:52,317
Pia.

355
00:36:01,410 --> 00:36:03,829
-Here.
-Hurry, hurry.

356
00:36:27,352 --> 00:36:28,520
This is my fault.

357
00:36:29,521 --> 00:36:32,816
I won't be able to forgive myself
if something happens to Eli.

358
00:36:34,359 --> 00:36:36,653
Anton, I tried to make you believe me.

359
00:36:37,279 --> 00:36:40,616
I tried to bring us back.
I tried to love you again.

360
00:36:40,699 --> 00:36:42,993
I know. But you got tired.

361
00:36:43,076 --> 00:36:45,996
I tried to trust you again.

362
00:36:46,079 --> 00:36:47,372
You gave up…

363
00:36:48,415 --> 00:36:50,250
while I made myself blind…

364
00:36:51,335 --> 00:36:53,462
because I wanted
to get you back from them.

365
00:36:56,548 --> 00:36:58,175
Get me back from who?

366
00:37:00,886 --> 00:37:03,055
Anton, what are you talking about?

367
00:37:03,138 --> 00:37:05,098
Tell it to me straight.

368
00:37:05,641 --> 00:37:07,100
You'll get me back from who?

369
00:37:21,782 --> 00:37:23,075
You know?

370
00:37:42,344 --> 00:37:44,888
Wait. Matteo, listen.

371
00:37:44,972 --> 00:37:47,641
Pia, Pia, there's Eli! Hurry up!

372
00:37:47,724 --> 00:37:48,558
Eli!

373
00:37:49,393 --> 00:37:51,269
Eli? Eli.

374
00:37:51,353 --> 00:37:52,938
-Matteo…
-Come on, Eli.

375
00:37:53,021 --> 00:37:54,231
Help him up.

376
00:37:54,314 --> 00:37:55,482
Matteo…

377
00:37:59,403 --> 00:38:00,529
Pa!

378
00:38:04,825 --> 00:38:06,118
Pa!

379
00:38:06,201 --> 00:38:07,828
Eli. Eli.

380
00:38:12,624 --> 00:38:13,458
Eli!

381
00:40:18,458 --> 00:40:20,669
I know you're mad at me.

382
00:40:22,420 --> 00:40:23,755
You should be.

383
00:40:24,589 --> 00:40:26,049
I understand.

384
00:40:30,971 --> 00:40:32,639
Did you really do that?

385
00:40:38,812 --> 00:40:41,189
Your mother saw me with another woman.

386
00:40:42,566 --> 00:40:43,942
It was years ago.

387
00:40:44,526 --> 00:40:46,069
I never did it again.

388
00:40:49,197 --> 00:40:52,200
I did everything to get
your mother to forgive me.

389
00:40:53,368 --> 00:40:55,537
So she wouldn't take you away from me.

390
00:40:57,581 --> 00:40:59,124
I'm so sorry.

391
00:41:01,001 --> 00:41:02,752
I'm sorry for everything.

392
00:41:06,381 --> 00:41:09,176
I told myself
that I wanted a boyfriend like you.

393
00:41:10,969 --> 00:41:12,304
But not anymore.

394
00:41:14,222 --> 00:41:16,474
I'm sorry for disappointing you.

395
00:41:20,228 --> 00:41:21,980
That apology…

396
00:41:22,063 --> 00:41:26,568
does that include making me feel useless
about what happened to Jem?

397
00:41:28,195 --> 00:41:30,113
As if you're a perfect man yourself.

398
00:41:30,697 --> 00:41:32,824
I just don't want you to end up like me.

399
00:41:32,908 --> 00:41:34,242
Just a few mistakes.

400
00:41:34,326 --> 00:41:38,163
It only takes a few mistakes
to ruin your life.

401
00:41:38,246 --> 00:41:39,748
And that's one of my regrets.

402
00:41:41,708 --> 00:41:43,251
You don't deserve Mama.

403
00:41:55,931 --> 00:41:58,099
That's why I'm giving up.

404
00:42:01,228 --> 00:42:03,730
I don't want to force her to forgive me.

405
00:42:07,567 --> 00:42:09,778
You can't give up!

406
00:42:09,861 --> 00:42:13,114
You don't get to decide
when you're giving up!

407
00:42:14,866 --> 00:42:16,910
I can't fix this anymore, Pia.

408
00:42:18,662 --> 00:42:19,913
I can't do it.

409
00:42:20,622 --> 00:42:23,250
Why… why would you give up?

410
00:42:23,333 --> 00:42:25,460
Mama endured it!

411
00:42:25,543 --> 00:42:26,711
Why can't you?

412
00:42:26,795 --> 00:42:28,922
Pa, you ruined our family!

413
00:42:29,005 --> 00:42:32,092
And now, you're giving up
because you can't fix it?

414
00:42:32,175 --> 00:42:35,095
Yes, I know. It's all my fault, Pia.

415
00:42:35,178 --> 00:42:37,347
I started this mess.

416
00:42:38,640 --> 00:42:41,017
But everything
that's happened to our family…

417
00:42:43,812 --> 00:42:45,188
it's not that simple.

418
00:42:45,272 --> 00:42:47,190
What? What's not simple?

419
00:42:48,024 --> 00:42:50,068
You cheated!

420
00:42:50,151 --> 00:42:52,696
And Mama had the courage to stay with you.

421
00:42:52,779 --> 00:42:54,864
It's that simple, Pa.

422
00:42:54,948 --> 00:42:56,992
You're so ungrateful.

423
00:42:57,075 --> 00:43:00,453
If I was her, I would've left long ago!

424
00:43:04,624 --> 00:43:08,086
I know she did everything
to keep our family together.

425
00:43:08,837 --> 00:43:11,423
But I also know that she's getting tired.

426
00:43:11,506 --> 00:43:15,302
Don't put the blame on her now.
Just please, don't you dare, Pa!

427
00:43:19,806 --> 00:43:20,849
If you split up,

428
00:43:21,850 --> 00:43:23,351
we're going with Mama.

429
00:43:23,435 --> 00:43:25,687
And you'll never see us again!

430
00:43:25,770 --> 00:43:28,481
I can't let that happen.
Please, Pia, Matt.

431
00:43:28,565 --> 00:43:29,607
That's unfair.

432
00:43:29,691 --> 00:43:30,817
Unfair?

433
00:43:30,900 --> 00:43:32,235
You're unfair!

434
00:43:33,403 --> 00:43:35,488
It's unfair to cheat on your own wife!

435
00:43:35,572 --> 00:43:36,823
Matteo is right.

436
00:43:37,407 --> 00:43:41,578
You chose to lose Mama.
And now, we choose to lose you!

437
00:43:41,661 --> 00:43:44,122
When you did that,
did you even think about us?

438
00:43:44,205 --> 00:43:46,249
Did you think about Eli?

439
00:43:46,333 --> 00:43:48,752
You're so selfish!

440
00:43:49,627 --> 00:43:52,088
You never thought about your own children!

441
00:43:52,172 --> 00:43:53,506
That's not true, Matt.

442
00:43:53,590 --> 00:43:55,925
-What's not true?
-Do you want to know the truth?

443
00:43:56,676 --> 00:43:58,511
Ask your mother, then.

444
00:43:58,595 --> 00:44:00,847
Ask her about her and Sam's relationship!
